row.column: Possible actions for a Legal Entity
Lifecycle status of a Legal Entity
Specifies that the message has been correctly sent and received by the receiver without any error. Typical result status: ACKED
Used for message attached to a netted transfer resulting in an amended to the message. Usually this action causes no change in object's status.
User marks the message as OK and ready for sending. Typical result status: VERIFIED
User cancels the message. Typical result status: CANCELED
User copy existing message and Save in DB
User copy existing message and Save in DB
User copy existing message and Save in DB
User edits the message, or user edits the trade, resulting in an edit to the message. Usually this action causes no change in object's status.
User corrects a NACKED message. This moves it to PENDING. This results in revalidating the Message -- to be implemented. Typical result status: PENDING
User puts message on hold. It cannot be sent until the hold is released. Typical result status: HELD
User indexes the message with some other message
User legal matches the message with some other message
Specifies that the receiver of the message has agreed with it. Typical result status: MATCHED
Specifies that the receiver of the message has NOT agreed with it. Typical result status: MISMATCHED
Specifies that the message was not correctly received. Typical result status: NACKED
User or system creates a new message. Typical result status: PENDING
User or system regenerates message advice document.
Not used by Calypso's default set-up.
User or system sends it to the recipient again. Typical result status: SENT
User or system sends it to the recipient. Typical result status: SENT
Send a Tracing Message in case no answer has been received from the Receiver of the Message.
Specify that the receiver of the message has not given any reply to the sent message. Typical result status: UNMATCHED
User updates messages with the current contacts
User allocates a trade. Typical result status: ALLOCATED
User edits the trade. Usually no change to status.
The Back Office authorizes the Trade. Generally, authorization occurs when all necessary details for Back-Office processing are OK. Typical result status: VERIFIED
User cancels trade. Typical result status: CANCELED
User continues trade. It means the current trade is ended but continued by another trade. It looks like a rollover.

User or system does basic verification to make sure trade contains needed data. In a front-to-back implementation, this is the typical action a trader performs to specify the trade has been executed with the counterparty. Typical result status: PENDING
User exercises option. Typical result status: EXERCISED
User adds trade to a hedge strategy
On or after maturity date, user marks trade as matured. Typical result status: MATURED
User merge a trade from a Cpty to another.
User enters new trade. Typical result status: PRICING
Floating interest payment is calculated, authorized and ready for payment. Usually no change to status.
Renewal of a Trade condition for CallNotice.
For repos and other open term trades, user rolls trade to extend maturity. Typical result status: ROLLBACKED
For repos and other open term trades, user rolls trade to extend maturity. Typical result status: ROLLOVERED
User splits a trade. Typical result status: CANCELED
User terminates trade before maturity. Typical result status: TERMINATED
User removes trade from a hedge strategy
User updates the trade. It is an internal amendment for adding information. No Confirmation or Ticket will be produced. Usually no change to status.
When Issued Yield To Price Conversion
User edits the transfer (payment), or user edits the trade, resulting in an edit to the transfer. Usually causes no change in object's status.
Assign settlement instructions to the transfer (XferAssign). The current transfer is canceled and replaced by a new one.
User marks transfer as checked and ready to be sent. Typical result status: VERIFIED
User cancels the transfer. Typical result status: CANCELED
User specifies that a netted transfer has been executed. Typical result status: VERIFIED
User specifies that the transfer has not been executed. Typical result status: FAILED
User puts transfer on hold. Typical result status: HELD
New transfer is created. Typical result status: PENDING
Partial Settle (pay or deliver) the transfer. User can specify the actual settlement date and the settlement amount which has been really settled. Typical result status: SPLIT
Not used by Calypso's default set-up
Settle (pay or deliver) the transfer. User can specify the actual settlement date and the settlement amount which has been really settled. Typical result status: SETTLED
User specifies that the transfer has not been splitted. Typical result status: SPLIT and 2 Transfers created
User specifies that the transfer is unassigned. Typical result status: CANCELED and 1 transfer created
User specifies that the transfer is unsplitted. Typical result status: CANCELED and 1 transfer created
Modification of the transfer which does not result in a cancel
Returns true if the trade is not allocated from a block trade.
Exercise action needs to be undone - it was applied by mistake.
Trade is accepted without settlements. SDI will be handled by the settlements team.
Trade is authorized manually by Trade Support.
Trade is amended by Trade Support. This action needs to be accepted / rejected by Supervisor.
Trade is cancelled by Trade Support. This action needs to be accepted / rejected by Supervisor.
This is a system action. No user should be allowed access to this action.
Trade is executed manually by FO.
"Trade is STP. CheckLimitNoExcess rule will need to be added to validate whether the trade satisfies the counterparty and trader limits. ERS system must be implemented for this rule to work."
Trade has been transferred to a different book.
Trade is amended by BO. This action needs to be accepted / rejected by Supervisor.
Trade is cancelled by BO. This action should be accepted / rejected by Supervisor.
